sharer, a time sharing system for the cdc .wa time sharing system embedded within thestandard batch processing system for the cdc  is described.  the system is general purpose and file-based,providing facilities for file input, manipulation, editing, compilation, and conversational execution. it uses a simple scheme for system extension for a machine with only one relocation and memory bound register. no attempt was made to use reentrant code, or to simulate segmentation or paging.  implementationtime was approximately six man-years, with the majority of the code being written in fortran.cacm october, harrison, m. c.schwartz, j. t.ca jb february ,  : pm